[head=3]Eviction of Survivors[/head]

Survivors can only be evicted or denied access to the ship in these cases: The [color=#01c4f6]Commanding Officer[/color] can overrule either decision and the [color=#007f00]Commander[/color] may overrule the [color=#cb0000]Chief MP[/color].

- Should a survivor commit a Major crime the [color=#007f00]Commander[/color] or [color=#cb0000]Chief MP[/color] may choose to evict them or refuse entrance to the Ship after their sentence has been completed. Once the survivor is evicted, they are barred from boarding the Ship again.

- Should the survivor be confirmed to have any confirmed ties to a military or paramilitary organization. The [color=#007f00]Commander[/color] or [color=#cb0000]Chief MP[/color] may bar the person from boarding.

- The Duty Officer, if there is one, is unable to evict survivors with the exception of where their crimes are of a violent nature.
